        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 6 at 12:20AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 1220 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Brinn to near Vernon. Movement was
northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cody, Henson Springs, Posey Field Airport, Houston Recreational Area,
Wayside, Richard Arthur Field, Clear Creek, Lynn, Ashbank, Rankin
Fite Airport, Fayette, Pebble, Upper Bear Creek Reservoir, Brushy
Lake, Guin, Pine Springs, Marion County Public Lake, Hightogy, Piney
Grove, and Crossville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 300 AM CDT for central,
northwestern and west central Alabama.</instruction>
